1
00:00:03,464 --> 00:00:07,960
This is one continuous operating session of Radeon Voice Skill Foundry.

2
00:00:07,960 --> 00:00:11,638
The workbench starts with a clean local data directory.

3
00:00:11,638 --> 00:00:17,360
The blue status badge shows how many trusted compile runs have been durably stored.

4
00:00:18,461 --> 00:00:26,400
I upload the same twenty-point-three-nine second spoken procedure used for the Radeon validation.

5
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:39,836
Voice Evidence version zero point two measures level, clipping, silence, noise floor, estimated signal-to-noise ratio, crest factor, dropout ratio, and source integrity.

6
00:00:39,836 --> 00:00:47,165
No acoustic diagnostic is triggered, and the source receives a one-hundred-out-of-one-hundred pass.

7
00:00:48,268 --> 00:00:53,631
Next, the transcript and aligned action trace are compiled into typed rules.

8
00:00:53,631 --> 00:01:03,909
The policy retrieves local evidence, keeps P-zero and P-one findings, redacts compensation data, requires confirmation for missing ownership, and denies automatic email sending.

9
00:01:03,909 --> 00:01:10,612
The trusted compile run is written to disk rather than kept only in process memory.

10
00:01:11,714 --> 00:01:16,038
The verifier executes seven positive and adversarial fixtures.

11
00:01:16,038 --> 00:01:19,822
The unsafe paths are tested before promotion.

12
00:01:19,822 --> 00:01:37,658
All seven pass, mail dot send remains denied, BLOCK and REVIEW receipts are issued, and the proof bundle receives a compatibility manifest for the verifier, runtime, tools, policy, skill, and voice evidence schema.

13
00:01:38,759 --> 00:01:45,387
The verified proof is saved into procedural memory with its original action contract.

14
00:01:45,387 --> 00:01:50,995
Exact reuse loads the proven skill without regenerating policy or fixtures.

15
00:01:50,995 --> 00:01:55,583
The reuse counter and measured retrieval latency update immediately.

16
00:01:56,685 --> 00:01:59,467
Now the application service is restarted.

17
00:01:59,467 --> 00:02:02,712
The browser stays in the same session.

18
00:02:02,712 --> 00:02:07,812
After reload, the saved skill and trusted proof are still available.

19
00:02:07,812 --> 00:02:15,693
The durable-run count survives because voice evidence, compile runs, and verification results are atomically persisted on disk.

20
00:02:16,795 --> 00:02:22,487
I restart the service again with a different runtime model identity.

21
00:02:22,487 --> 00:02:26,627
The saved proof is no longer silently trusted.

22
00:02:26,627 --> 00:02:35,424
The skill changes to revalidation required and explains that the model, GPU, ROCm, or runtime contract changed.

23
00:02:35,424 --> 00:02:38,011
The Reuse command becomes Revalidate.

24
00:02:39,113 --> 00:02:50,136
Revalidation creates a new child run bound to the current runtime, reruns all seven fixtures, and produces a new compatible proof.

25
00:02:50,136 --> 00:02:53,285
The skill returns to verified status.

26
00:02:53,285 --> 00:03:03,259
Finally, I download the proof package containing the skill, policy, fixtures, receipts, local evidence, voice evidence, and compatibility manifest.

27
00:03:03,259 --> 00:03:09,550
This completes the full lifecycle from voice to policy to proof, through restart, invalidation, and recovery.
